text: International rules football () is a team sport that is a hybrid of two football codes: Australian rules football and Gaelic football. It was created for the International Rules Series, where Australia and Ireland play each other. ==Related pages== * Comparison of Gaelic football and Australian rules football ** Irish experiment * List of countries playing Australian rules football ** List of national Australian rules football teams * List of Gaelic games clubs outside Ireland ==References== Category:Football
title: International rules football
